  <formalMetadata>
    <description>A set of web pages - the web site of the fictitious newspaper The Narnia Times - that has a top navigation section at the top of each page.
      None of these pages has a link at the top to skip the navigation and go directly to the main content area.
    </description>
    <title>Set of web pages without a link to skip the navigation</title>
    <dc:creator>Christophe.Strobbe@esat.kuleuven.be</dc:creator>
    <dc:language>en</dc:language>
    <dc:rights>Copyright BenToWeb 2004-2007</dc:rights>
    <date>2006-10-11</date>
    <status>validated</status>
  </formalMetadata>
  <technology>
    <recommendation xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/">
      <label><html:acronym>XHTML</html:acronym>â„¢ 1.0 The Extensible HyperText Markup Language (Second Edition)</label>
      <testElements>
        <testElement>
          <elementName localname="a" namespace="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>
          <specReference xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/1999/REC-html401-19991224/struct/links.html#edef-A">The <html:code>A</html:code> element</specReference>
        </testElement>
      </testElements>
    </recommendation>
  </technology>
  <testCase complexity="atomic">
    <purpose>
      <p>This test case is intended to fail because there is no mechanism to skip the navigation at the top of every page.</p>
    </purpose>
    <requiredTests>
      <testModes>
        <testMode>oneExpert</testMode>
      </testModes>
    </requiredTests>
    <files>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004.html"/>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_arts.html"/>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_world.html"/>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_business.html"/>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_sports.html"/>
      <file hrefLang="en" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_jobs.html"/>
    </files>
  </testCase>
  <rules>
    <rule id="http://bentoweb.org/refs/rulesets.xml#WCAG2_20070517_2.4_navigation-mechanisms-title" primary="yes">
      <locations expectedResult="fail">
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_arts.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_world.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_business.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_sports.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_jobs.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
      </locations>
      <functionalOutcome>
        <p>Users who rely on keyboard navigation are forced to tab through all the navigation links before getting to the content.</p>
      </functionalOutcome>
      <techComment>
        <p>This test case maps to technique <html:span class="technique"><html:a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2007/WD-WCAG20-TECHS-20070517/#G1">G1: Adding a link at the top of each page that goes directly to the main content area</html:a>
                    </html:span> but fails.</p>
      </techComment>
    </rule>
    <rule id="http://bentoweb.org/refs/rulesets.xml#WCAG2_20060427_2.4_navigation-mechanisms-title" primary="no">
      <locations expectedResult="fail">
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_arts.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_world.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_business.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_sports.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
        <location column="1" line="19" xlink:href="../testfiles/sc2.4.1_l1_004_jobs.html" xpath="/h:html/h:body/h:div[@id='top']"/>
      </locations>
      <functionalOutcome>
        <p>Users who rely on keyboard navigation are forced to tab through all the navigation links before getting to the content.</p>
      </functionalOutcome>
      <techComment>
        <p>This test case maps to technique G1: Adding a link at the top of each page that goes directly to the main content area (http://www.w3.org/TR/2006/WD-WCAG20-TECHS-20060427/Overview.html#G1) but fails.</p>
        <p>Online version: <html:span><html:a href="http://www.bentoweb.org/ts/XHTML1_TestSuite2/metadata/sc2.4.1_l1_004">sc2.4.1_l1_004</html:a></html:span>.</p>
      </techComment>
    </rule>
  </rules>
